FBIS4-35037 "drlat124_n_94008" FBIS-LAT-94-124 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 Chile Correa: Problem With Teachers, Miners `Serious' Correa: Problem With Teachers, Miners `Serious' PY2706142294 Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen Internacional in Spanish 1100 GMT 27 Jun 94 PY2706142294 Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen Internacional Spanish BFN [Text] Vice President German Correa admitted that Chile is currently facing very serious problems. One of them concerns teachers and the other coal miners: [Begin Correa recording] These are long-lasting problems. They are not being politicized although some may be tempted to do so. For the time being, however, we have not detected any politicization of the situation. These are serious problems but the government is striving to resolve them promptly and with the dignity they deserve. [end recording]
